<subSubSection id="C3428CD9FFE4FFB1FF77C8CDFE9D7665" pageId="12" pageNumber="139" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BE7DF52FFE4FFB1FF77C8CDFE9D7665" blockId="12.[151,1437,151,789]" pageId="12" pageNumber="139">
<emphasis id="B92C0340FFE4FFB1FF77C8CDFEC077BD" bold="true" box="[199,334,692,717]" pageId="12" pageNumber="139">Etymology.</emphasis>
The species is named after Sander Bot’s girlfriend, 
<taxonomicName id="4C58A4D1FFE4FFB1FC74C8CCFB8A77BC" box="[964,1028,693,716]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Microdon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="138" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="janne">Janne</taxonomicName>
Ouwehand, since for long Sander promised her to name after her the first new species for science he would describe. The epithet is a noun in apposition.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
